org.presentation.model.logging

Interface MessageMapper

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    MessageMapperImpl

    public interface MessageMapper
    This interface should serve as object for conversion between some specific kind of Message or other similar object. Specific implementation is used for conversion between the hierarchical object tree of these elements to classes with linear instance fields which are used especially for persisting into database.
    Author:
    radio.koza

    • Method Detail

      • setMessage

        void setMessage(String message)
        Set string message to implemented instance of MessageMapper.
        Parameters:
        message - String representing information about message

      • setPage

        void setPage(LinkURL linkURL)
        Set url of message source to implemented instance of MessageMapper.
        Parameters:
        linkURL - LinkURL object representing url of the message source

      • setMsgLocation

        void setMsgLocation(MsgLocation msgLocation)
        Set location to point on source of the message. This parameter is voluntary in message and it is not necessary to be called. Implementations must not require calling this method.
        Parameters:
        msgLocation - MsgLocation class instance representing source of method

      • setErrorCode

        void setErrorCode(ResponseCode errorCode)
        Set error code for this message. This method should be called only on messages where the error code is known, Implementations must not require calling this method, because this argument is voluntary in some kinds of message implementations.
        Parameters:
        errorCode - ResponseCode class instance representing the error code number. (e.g. 404 for Not Found)

      • setPriority

        void setPriority(Integer priority)
        Set priority for this message.
        Parameters:
        priority - Message priority in integer; priority must be valid or the IllegalArgumentException will be thrown by the specific implementation of Message

      • getMessage

        String getMessage()
        Retrieve message string from the message mapped class. Method is used to reconstruct instance of Message implementation from the mapped class.
        Returns:
        String representing information about message

      • getPage

        LinkURL getPage()
        Retrieve page from the message mapped class.
        Returns:
        LinkURL class instance representing link of page which the message is connected with

      • getMsgLocation

        MsgLocation getMsgLocation()
        Retrieve message location from the message mapped class.
        Returns:
        MsgLocation class instance representing location of page that the message was created from

      • getErrorCode

        ResponseCode getErrorCode()
        Retrieve error code of the message. Note that error code can be null in case the mapped message object is not representing implementation of message which does not have error code by itself.
        Returns:
        ResponseCode class instance representing error code.

      • getPriority

        Integer getPriority()
        Retrieve priority of the message.
        Returns:
        Integer priority of message.

      • setDiscriminator

        void setDiscriminator(String discriminator)
        Set disciminator of this message. Discriminator is the full class name of the Message object implementation and it must be possible to instantiate the message implementing object by use of java reflection feature.
        Parameters:
        discriminator - String of fully represented class name of the specific implementation of the Message; it is created by calling Class.getName() method of the specific message implementation
